aiResponses.summary: Product-focused technology professional with a strong blend of product management, analytics and hands-on technical skills. Experienced in Agile practices (Scrum, Kanban), roadmap planning, and building data-driven decision processes using Tableau, Power BI, SQL and Python. Comfortable bridging engineering and business teams to deliver customer-centered solutions.

workExperience.title: Product Manager
workExperience.highlights: At SYNYCS TECHNOLOGIES I led cross-functional teams through Agile ceremonies using Jira and Scrum, translating customer feedback into prioritized backlog items and product enhancements. I partnered closely with engineering to scope features and with analytics to instrument product behavior, using Python and SQL to validate hypotheses and Tableau/Power BI to monitor impact. I drove iterative releases and coordinated stakeholder communications, improving alignment between engineering, design and commercial teams.

workExperience.title: Technical Project Lead
workExperience.highlights: At theworkgallery.com I focused on operationalizing analytics and building user-focused features. I implemented Google Analytics and custom dashboards to track user journeys and conversions, collaborated with front-end developers on React-based interfaces, and used Lean Startup principles to run experiments that informed roadmap direction. I also organized sprint planning and used Trello/Kanban to streamline delivery across distributed teams.

aiResponses.coverLetter:
I am excited to apply for roles where I can bring together my product management experience, technical background, and analytics skills to create measurable customer value. Throughout my career I have worked at the intersection of engineering, data, and user experience â€” at SYNYCS TECHNOLOGIES I translated user research and stakeholder priorities into a clear product backlog and coordinated cross-functional sprints using Jira and Scrum. I partnered with data engineers and analysts to instrument features and built Tableau and Power BI dashboards that made performance visible to the entire organization, enabling faster, data-driven decisions.

At theworkgallery.com I embraced Lean Startup practices to run rapid experiments and validate product hypotheses. I collaborated with front-end engineers working in React to deliver user-facing improvements while using SQL and Python to analyze behavioral data and guide prioritization. These experiences sharpened my ability to communicate technical constraints to non-technical stakeholders and to convert insights into pragmatic roadmaps and deliverables.

I bring not only technical fluency but also a culture-first approach: I value transparent communication, continuous improvement, and mentorship. I enjoy creating the processes and measurement practices that help teams move faster and with confidence. I am enthusiastic about opportunities where I can apply my mix of analytics, product strategy, and hands-on execution to help teams build products customers love.
